This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. By Lawrence Enyoghasu, Lagos Nollywood Actor Ugo Spunky has announced his new ambassadorial deal with a real estate company, Nairalandhomes. The actor took to social media to announce his new feat to his fans and followers. He wrote: ‘Fam Good news, Let me introduce you to my new family @nairalandhomes as their latest ambassador. The best plug for properties and homes. I’m excited about this one.’ Nairalandhomes in a post on Instagram also welcomed him to the family. Spunky hails from South East Nigeria, Ogberuru in Orlu Local Government Area, Imo State. His acting career kicked off as a kid but he officially joined Nollywood in 2014. Where he has played lead and sub-lead characters in numerous movies, such as “The Throne”, “Touch of a Ghost”, “Fight to Finish”, “Streak of Fate”, “Beautiful Players”, “Dis and Dat”, “Destiny of the Blind”, and “Sugar Boy”.